Observations :

  1. Over a period of 147 years (the data that we have) from '1872-11-30' to '2019-07-20', football matches have been played on 15115 distinct days with one or more matches being played on a particular day.
  2. Most no. of matches(equal to 63) were played on a single day, i.e. Feb 29,2012.
  3. There are a total of 309 unique teams who have played 40839 mathces on home ground with Brazil playing the most number of matches (equal to 563) on home ground(in the same country).
  4. There are a total of 306 unique teams who have played 40839 mathces away from the home ground on in neutral venue with Uruguay playing the most number of matches (equal to 536) on in other countries.
  5. All the teams played football matches under 109 different tournaments with most matches (equal to 16911) were played under the Friendly tournaments.
  6. All the Football matches were played across 1960 unique cities across 266 distinct countries with most number of matches being played in the Kuala Lumpur city.
  7. It can be observed that the most number of matches (equal to 1144) were played in United States.
  8. Out of 40839 matches, 10159 matches were played on neutral venues.

Feature Engineering - Adding New Features¶

In [18]:
df['home_won'] = [1 if i>j else 0 for i,j in zip(df.home_score,df.away_score)]
df['away_won'] = [1 if i<j else 0 for i,j in zip(df.home_score,df.away_score)]
df['drawn'] = [1 if i==j else 0 for i,j in zip(df.home_score,df.away_score)]
df['year'] = df['date'].apply(lambda x : x[0:4]).astype(int)
In [19]:
df['winning_team'] = np.where((df['home_won'] == 1), df['home_team'], df['away_team'])
df['winning_team'] = np.where((df['drawn'] == 1), 'NoResult', df['winning_team'])

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)¶

In [21]:
df.dtypes
Out[21]:
date            object
home_team       object
away_team       object
home_score       int64
away_score       int64
tournament      object
city            object
country         object
neutral           bool
home_won         int64
away_won         int64
drawn            int64
year             int32
winning_team    object
dtype: object

Observations :

  1. 'home_score' and 'away_score' are integer features which describes the goals scored by home and away team resp.
  2. Except the 'date' feature, which reprents the date of the match, the rest of the object types features are categorical features like 'home_team', 'away_team','tournament', 'city', 'country'.
  3. 'home_team' and 'country' features have the same values except for some observations where it is different becuase the the name of country was different at the time, the match was played. But such records are taken care of by setting the neutral feature to 'False'.
  4. 'neutral' is a boolean feature which describes the type of venue for the match, i.e. whether it is a home venue for the home team or not. If home venue, the value is 'False' otherwise 'True'.

In [75]:
# Using the elbow method to find the optimal number of clusters

wcss = []
for i in range(1, 11):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters = i, init = 'k-means++', random_state = 42)
    kmeans.fit(X)
    wcss.append(kmeans.inertia_)
plt.plot(range(1, 11), wcss)
plt.title('The Elbow Method')
plt.xlabel('Number of clusters')
plt.ylabel('WCSS')
plt.show()

We can select the optimum no of clusters to be 4 from the above graph.
